    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-02-06T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-02-06T02:00:00-05:00" n="785"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4d/120: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-02-06T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1926—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 6—7:46 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>66. Last sentence of your 36. I concur fully in your proposal that you deliver
                    your intended note to the Chinese Minister without awaiting further action by
                    him, telegraphing the text of the note to me for use as suggested in my telegram
                    50, January 27, noon, first paragraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
